辰.definition: 5th earthly branch: 7-9 a.m., 3rd solar month (5th April-4th May), year of the Dragon; ancient Chinese compass point: 120°

辰光.definition: sunlight; (Wu dialect) time of the day; moment

辰星.definition: Mercury in traditional Chinese astronomy; see also 水星[shui3 xing1]

辰時.definition: 7-9 am (in the system of two-hour subdivisions used in former times)

辰溪.definition: Chenxi county in Huaihua 懷化|怀化[Huai2 hua4], Hunan

辰溪縣.definition: Chenxi county in Huaihua 懷化|怀化[Huai2 hua4], Hunan
